WEBVTT

00:00.901 --> 00:03.635
[ DOOR OPENS ]

00:03.637 --> 00:07.373
♪♪

00:07.375 --> 00:11.727
WE HAVE HIS BASEBALL JERSEY
IN HERE FROM LITTLE LEAGUE

00:11.729 --> 00:13.962
WHEN HE PLAYED.

00:13.964 --> 00:17.733
TEXAS, 2, DAIGLE.

00:17.735 --> 00:20.602
THE EXPERIENCE OF NOT KNOWING
WHERE YOUR CHILD IS

00:20.604 --> 00:23.322
AND IF HE'S OKAY,
IT'S REALLY HARD.

00:23.324 --> 00:25.307
YOU CAN'T SLEEP AT NIGHT.

00:25.309 --> 00:26.692
YOU'RE CONSTANTLY LOOKING.

00:26.694 --> 00:29.945
♪♪

00:31.198 --> 00:34.649
I WANT TO BE VERY CAREFUL
WITH WHAT I SAY.

00:34.651 --> 00:37.870
HE STARTED TO TURN INTO
SOMEBODY ELSE.

00:37.872 --> 00:40.672
Samantha: YOUR MIND GOES TO
THE MOST HORRIBLE PLACES.

00:40.674 --> 00:44.593
THIS WAS A REPEATED THING
FOR 10 YEARS.

00:44.595 --> 00:46.845
Tracie: I'D SEE SOMEBODY THAT
COULD POSSIBLY LOOK LIKE HIM.

00:46.847 --> 00:48.847
I WOULD FOLLOW HIM.

00:48.849 --> 00:51.016
AND THEN I WOULD HAVE TO
EXPLAIN MYSELF TO THEM,

00:51.018 --> 00:53.018
"I'M NOT CRAZY.

00:53.020 --> 00:55.270
I'M JUST TRYING
TO FIND MY SON."

00:55.272 --> 00:58.557
♪♪

01:02.980 --> 01:06.198
-- Captions by VITAC --
 www.vitac.com

01:06.200 --> 01:09.651
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

01:23.033 --> 01:26.635
Tracie: THE LAST DAY THAT
WE REMEMBER SEEING CHRIS

01:26.637 --> 01:27.886
WAS NOVEMBER THE 7th.

01:27.888 --> 01:29.004
HE WENT TO SCHOOL
THAT MORNING.

01:29.006 --> 01:32.391
MY MOM TOOK HIM.

01:32.393 --> 01:34.510
MY MOM SAID CHRIS
WAS DEPRESSED

01:34.512 --> 01:38.213
AND HE WAS TIRED OF
GOING TO SCHOOL EVERY DAY

01:38.215 --> 01:40.382
AND BEING TOLD WHAT TO DO.

01:40.384 --> 01:42.351
ARE YOU OKAY, CHRIS?

01:42.353 --> 01:44.269
YEAH.
I'M ALL RIGHT, GRANDMA.

01:46.941 --> 01:48.857
I'LL SEE YOU
AFTER SCHOOL, HONEY.

01:52.113 --> 01:56.248
HE JUST WASN'T HAPPY,
AND THAT WASN'T LIKE HIM.

01:56.250 --> 01:59.368
♪♪

02:05.926 --> 02:08.177
Narrator: A JUNIOR AT
HIGH TOWER HIGH SCHOOL,

02:08.179 --> 02:13.799
17-YEAR-OLD CHRISTOPHER DAIGLE
WAS ONE OF THE POPULAR KIDS.

02:13.801 --> 02:15.750
CHRIS WAS TALL, HANDSOME.

02:15.752 --> 02:17.586
I MEAN,
ALWAYS DRESSED NICE

02:17.588 --> 02:20.922
AND CUTE AND DEFINITELY
A HEAD-TURNER,

02:20.924 --> 02:23.892
ALWAYS COULD MAKE YOU LAUGH.

02:23.894 --> 02:25.694
ALL THE GUYS WANTED
TO HANG OUT WITH HIM

02:25.696 --> 02:28.096
AND THE GIRLS
MOST DEFINITELY,

02:28.098 --> 02:31.950
THEY WANTED A CHANCE
TO BE WITH HIM.

02:31.952 --> 02:35.204
I'M TRYING TO KEEP FROM
USING "SMART-ASS,"

02:35.206 --> 02:37.956
BECAUSE THAT'S THE BEST TERM
TO DESCRIBE HIM.

02:37.958 --> 02:38.957
TEACH.

02:38.959 --> 02:42.494
HE HAD THIS WAY ABOUT HIM

02:42.496 --> 02:47.115
TO WHERE HE COULD, UM,
SUGGEST SOMETHING WITH A SMILE

02:47.117 --> 02:49.084
AND THEN THAT WAS IT,
EVERYBODY WAS LIKE,

02:49.086 --> 02:52.137
"YEAH, YEAH,
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA."

02:52.139 --> 02:55.641
Narrator: AND NO ONE KNOWS CHRIS
BETTER THAN HIS GRANDMA WANDA,

02:55.643 --> 02:59.094
WHO HE HAS BEEN LIVING WITH
SINCE HE WAS THREE.

02:59.096 --> 03:01.096
Tracie: SHE COULD TAKE
BETTER CARE OF HIM

03:01.098 --> 03:03.148
THAN I COULD
AS FAR AS FINANCIALLY.

03:03.150 --> 03:04.483
SHE SPOILED HIM ROTTEN.

03:04.485 --> 03:09.154
SHE GOT HIM MOTORCYCLES,
FOUR-WHEELERS, THREE-WHEELERS.

03:09.156 --> 03:12.524
ANYTHING HE WANTED, HE GOT.

03:12.526 --> 03:15.611
SHE ENDED UP GETTING HIM
THE K5 BLAZER,

03:15.613 --> 03:19.147
WHICH HE LOVED THAT.

03:19.149 --> 03:21.500
SHE REALLY
TOOK CARE OF HIM.

03:21.502 --> 03:24.036
Samantha: HE LOVED HIS GRANDMA.

03:24.038 --> 03:25.704
HE COULD BE MAD
AS THE DEVIL AT HER,

03:25.706 --> 03:28.757
BUT HE'D HAVE NEVER LEFT HER.

03:28.759 --> 03:30.008
NEVER.

03:33.514 --> 03:36.331
Narrator: THE NIGHT AFTER WANDA
DROPPED CHRIS OFF AT SCHOOL,

03:36.333 --> 03:40.385
DINNERTIME COMES AND GOES,
BUT CHRIS NEVER SHOWS UP.

03:43.023 --> 03:45.173
WE THOUGHT HE WAS
JUST SPENDING THE NIGHT

03:45.175 --> 03:48.026
WITH SOME OF HIS FRIENDS
AND THAT HE WOULD JUST

03:48.028 --> 03:50.345
COME HOME THE NEXT DAY,
AND USUALLY,

03:50.347 --> 03:52.447
IF HE DIDN'T COME HOME,
WE DIDN'T WORRY.

03:52.449 --> 03:54.866
HE WAS ALWAYS
WITH HIS FRIENDS.

03:54.868 --> 03:58.070
♪♪

04:02.693 --> 04:04.042
THE FOLLOWING MORNING,

04:04.044 --> 04:06.295
THERE'S STILL
NO WORD FROM CHRIS,

04:06.297 --> 04:09.548
AND CALLS TO HIS CELL PHONE
GO UNANSWERED.

04:11.385 --> 04:13.635
HIS FAMILY REACHES OUT
TO HIS FRIENDS,

04:13.637 --> 04:16.755
STARTING WITH BRITTANY PARKER.

04:16.757 --> 04:19.591
Brittany: CHRIS WENT
TO SCHOOL THAT DAY

04:19.593 --> 04:22.261
AND THEN HE HAD COME BY MY HOUSE
FOR A LITTLE BIT.

04:22.263 --> 04:25.063
HIS STATE OF MIND
WASN'T ANYTHING

04:25.065 --> 04:26.682
OUT OF THE NORMAL FOR HIM.

04:26.684 --> 04:27.849
HE LEFT.

04:27.851 --> 04:32.053
HE WENT OVER TO
OUR FRIEND ASHLEY'S HOUSE.

04:32.055 --> 04:35.824
HE GOT A PHONE CALL THAT, "HEY,
YOU WANT TO GO DO THIS OR THAT?"

04:35.826 --> 04:38.827
AND HE SAID YEAH AND HE WAS
PICKED UP BY HIS FRIEND, RICKY.

04:38.829 --> 04:39.995
HEY, HIT MY HOUSE FIRST.

04:39.997 --> 04:43.565
GOT YOU.

04:43.567 --> 04:45.584
Samantha: AND EVERYONE SAW
A TRUCK PULL UP,

04:45.586 --> 04:47.536
AND HE GOT A DUFFEL BAG,
THREW IT IN

04:47.538 --> 04:49.705
THE BACK OF THE TRUCK,
AND THEY TOOK OFF,

04:49.707 --> 04:53.625
AND THAT WAS THE LAST TIME
ANYBODY SAW HIM HERE

04:53.627 --> 04:55.243
OTHER THAN HIS FRIENDS.

04:55.245 --> 04:57.796
Narrator: HIS GOOD FRIEND RICKY
SAYS HE AND CHRIS

04:57.798 --> 04:59.881
DROVE TO THE NEARBY MALL
TO HANG OUT.

04:59.883 --> 05:01.350
HEY, MAN.
TAKE A LOOK.

05:01.352 --> 05:03.418
Jen: RICKY HAD JUST SAID THAT
THEY'D SEEN SOME GIRLS THERE.

05:03.420 --> 05:04.853
WANT TO GO TALK TO THEM
FOR A LITTLE BIT?

05:04.855 --> 05:08.106
YOU GOING TO HANG OUT?
NO, I'VE GOT TO GO.

05:08.108 --> 05:09.858
YOU SURE?

05:09.860 --> 05:11.426
THEY WANTED TO LEAVE
AND GO SOME PLACE,

05:11.428 --> 05:14.646
BUT RICKY'S MOM CALLED HIM,
TOLD HIM HE HAD TO COME HOME,

05:14.648 --> 05:16.448
SO CHRIS LEFT WITH THE GIRLS.

05:16.450 --> 05:18.450
I'LL SEE YOU LATER,
OKAY?

05:18.452 --> 05:19.818
ALL RIGHT,
HAVE FUN.

05:19.820 --> 05:22.954
Narrator: BUT NO ONE KNOWS
ANYTHING ABOUT THESE GIRLS,

05:22.956 --> 05:25.957
NOT EVEN THEIR NAMES.

05:25.959 --> 05:30.045
Tracie: NOBODY SEEMED TO KNOW
WHERE HE HAD GONE.

05:30.047 --> 05:31.913
I'D HEAR OF
OTHER PEOPLE MISSING.

05:31.915 --> 05:34.099
I NEVER THOUGHT IT WOULD
HAPPEN TO ME.

05:37.421 --> 05:38.804
CHRIS WAS ALWAYS SO MUCH FUN,

05:38.806 --> 05:41.006
ALWAYS PLAYING
AND RUNNING AROUND,

05:41.008 --> 05:43.475
AND HE WAS A DAREDEVIL.

05:43.477 --> 05:44.793
WHEN HE WAS
LIKE THREE YEARS OLD,

05:44.795 --> 05:46.928
HE WOULD TRY ANYTHING.

05:46.930 --> 05:49.964
HE DIDN'T LIKE
THE WORD "NO."

05:49.966 --> 05:51.600
IF YOU'D TELL HIM NO,
HE COULDN'T DO SOMETHING,

05:51.602 --> 05:54.403
HE WAS GOING TO DO IT
JUST TO SHOW YOU HE COULD DO IT.

05:54.405 --> 05:58.523
♪♪

05:58.525 --> 06:01.743
DEFINITELY 100-PERCENT ALL-BOY.

06:03.280 --> 06:06.248
[ THWACK ]

06:06.250 --> 06:08.834
Tracie: HE STARTED
PLAYING BASEBALL

06:08.836 --> 06:10.702
WHEN HE WAS FIVE YEARS OLD,

06:10.704 --> 06:13.839
AND HE WAS ON SELECT TEAMS
AND THEN HE WENT TO HIGH SCHOOL

06:13.841 --> 06:17.959
AND HE PLAYED ON HIGH TOWER
HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL.

06:17.961 --> 06:19.544
CHRIS WAS VERY TALENTED.

06:19.546 --> 06:22.214
I WAS VERY, YOU KNOW, HAPPY

06:22.216 --> 06:25.267
AND JUST ALWAYS BRAGGED
ABOUT HOW GOOD HE WAS.

06:25.269 --> 06:26.551
HEADS UP.

06:26.553 --> 06:30.389
YOU KNOW YOU ONLY GET
THREE STRIKES, RIGHT?

06:30.391 --> 06:33.007
ONE, TWO, THREE,
AND THAT'S IT.

06:33.009 --> 06:35.227
YEAH, SURE.
BRING IT.

06:35.229 --> 06:36.561
HE WOULD HAVE
GOT SCHOLARSHIPS.

06:36.563 --> 06:40.849
I MEAN, HE WAS --
HE WAS REALLY GOOD.

06:40.851 --> 06:44.069
Tracie: CHRIS WOULD
DREAM ABOUT IT,

06:44.071 --> 06:47.021
RUNNING AND TELLING PEOPLE,
"NO, HE'S OUT AT FIRST BASE,"

06:47.023 --> 06:48.790
AND JUST I COULDN'T BELIEVE

06:48.792 --> 06:52.210
THAT HE COULD HAVE
A BASEBALL GAME IN HIS SLEEP.

06:52.212 --> 06:55.213
♪♪

06:56.633 --> 06:59.033
Narrator: BUT IN THE SUMMER
BEFORE HIS SENIOR YEAR,

06:59.035 --> 07:02.003
CHRIS' MAJOR LEAGUE DREAMS
ARE SHATTERED.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.758
♪♪

07:06.760 --> 07:11.596
Tracie: THERE WAS AN INCIDENT
WHERE SOMEBODY THREW A BOTTLE

07:11.598 --> 07:13.214
AND IT HIT CHRIS,

07:13.216 --> 07:15.016
SO CHRIS GOT MAD
AND THREW IT BACK

07:15.018 --> 07:18.236
AND IT HIT THE COACH.

07:18.238 --> 07:19.387
THAT WAS IT.

07:19.389 --> 07:22.524
THREW HIM OFF THE TEAM.

07:22.526 --> 07:24.559
Brittany: WHEN HE GOT
KICKED OFF THE BASEBALL TEAM,

07:24.561 --> 07:27.913
THAT WAS --
THAT WAS DEVASTATING FOR HIM.

07:27.915 --> 07:30.332
THAT WAS, LIKE,
WORLD-CRUSHING.

07:30.334 --> 07:33.201
♪♪

07:38.592 --> 07:41.126
ARE YOU OKAY, CHRIS?

07:43.130 --> 07:46.181
YEAH.
I'M ALL RIGHT, GRANDMA.

07:46.183 --> 07:47.582
OKAY, HONEY.

07:47.584 --> 07:49.935
YOU KIND OF SAW
THIS LIGHT IN HIM

07:49.937 --> 07:51.553
KIND OF START
TO DIM A LITTLE BIT,

07:51.555 --> 07:53.054
AND HE CHANGED.

07:56.092 --> 08:00.729
HE STARTED TO TURN
INTO SOMEBODY ELSE.

08:00.731 --> 08:02.781
Tracie: HE REALLY DIDN'T
ASSOCIATE WITH HIS FRIENDS

08:02.783 --> 08:07.435
AS MUCH AS HE DID
AFTER THAT HAPPENED.

08:07.437 --> 08:09.955
HE WAS HURTING.

08:13.410 --> 08:14.960
Narrator: THE FOLLOWING DAY,

08:14.962 --> 08:18.079
CHRIS DOESN'T SHOW UP
TO SCHOOL AT ALL.

08:18.081 --> 08:20.298
Brittany: IT WASN'T,
LIKE, CONCERNING.

08:20.300 --> 08:21.466
IT WASN'T A BIG DEAL.

08:21.468 --> 08:24.252
OKAY, SO HE SKIPPED SCHOOL,
OR, YOU KNOW,

08:24.254 --> 08:26.888
HE'S DOING SOMETHING ELSE.

08:26.890 --> 08:28.590
WHEN I GO HOME,
I CALL HIM,

08:28.592 --> 08:29.925
HE DOESN'T ANSWER.

08:29.927 --> 08:31.793
CALL HIM A COUPLE OF MORE TIMES,
HE DOESN'T ANSWER.

08:31.795 --> 08:33.144
STARTED TALKING TO
SOME OTHER FRIENDS.

08:33.146 --> 08:35.129
"OKAY, WELL, WHERE IS CHRIS?
HAS ANYBODY SEEN HIM?

08:35.131 --> 08:36.965
NO? NOBODY'S SPOKEN WITH HIM?

08:36.967 --> 08:39.100
THAT'S NOT RIGHT."

08:39.102 --> 08:41.903
Jen: I REMEMBER MY GRANDMA
CALLING ME AND I WAS JUST LIKE,

08:41.905 --> 08:45.156
"WHAT DO YOU MEAN, MISSING?
LIKE, HE RAN AWAY?"

08:45.158 --> 08:47.909
THAT'S WHAT
I FIGURED IT WAS.

08:47.911 --> 08:51.196
Narrator: SOME OF CHRIS' FRIENDS
THINK THE DUFFEL BAG SUGGESTS

08:51.198 --> 08:53.782
HE WAS LEAVING FOR GOOD.

08:53.784 --> 08:55.483
Jen: WHEN HE LOST BASEBALL,

08:55.485 --> 08:58.753
HE WAS SAD AND HE WAS
MAD AND ANGRY

08:58.755 --> 09:00.171
AND HE WAS LIKE,
"I'M MOVING.

09:00.173 --> 09:02.156
I'M GOING TO LEAVE,
I'M GOING TO RUN AWAY."

09:02.158 --> 09:03.925
Zavala: YOU KNOW,
YOU HAVE TO THINK ABOUT

09:03.927 --> 09:06.545
THE MIND IN ADOLESCENTS,
IN 16 AND 17.

09:06.547 --> 09:11.499
SOMETHING MINOR
IN THEIR WORLD IS HUGE

09:11.501 --> 09:13.852
AND THEY FEEL LIKE
THEY CAN'T HANDLE IT ANYMORE.

09:17.724 --> 09:19.474
Samantha: I THOUGHT
HE JUST TOOK OFF.

09:19.476 --> 09:21.443
JUST HIM AND HIS FRIENDS
WERE GOING TO GO

09:21.445 --> 09:24.112
TO THE BEACH FOR A FEW DAYS.

09:24.114 --> 09:27.148
HE WAS JUST GOING TO HAUL ASS
FOR A FEW DAYS

09:27.150 --> 09:28.333
AND THEN HE WOULD BE BACK.

09:28.335 --> 09:31.536
Narrator: BUT ACCORDING
TO CHRIS' FRIENDS,

09:31.538 --> 09:34.122
IN THE MONTHS AFTER
GETTING KICKED OFF THE TEAM,

09:34.124 --> 09:37.542
HIS BEHAVIOR CHANGED.

09:37.544 --> 09:40.829
I WANT TO BE VERY CAREFUL
WITH WHAT I SAY.

09:40.831 --> 09:44.799
HE STARTED TO
MAKE SOME DECISIONS

09:44.801 --> 09:48.053
THAT I KNOW THAT HE WASN'T
SUPER PROUD OF.

09:48.055 --> 09:51.056
HE STARTED TO PARTY
A LOT MORE.

09:51.058 --> 09:52.557
HE DIDN'T CARE SO MUCH,

09:52.559 --> 09:56.094
BECAUSE THE ONE THING THAT HE
REALLY WAS PASSIONATE ABOUT

09:56.096 --> 09:57.929
WAS KIND OF
STRIPPED FROM HIM.

09:57.931 --> 10:00.315
Narrator: BUT IF CHRIS IS
RUNNING AWAY FROM HIS PROBLEMS,

10:00.317 --> 10:04.436
HE HAS NO IDEA THE TROUBLE
HE IS HEADING INTO.

10:04.438 --> 10:07.339
Samantha: PEOPLE ARE CRAZY.
THEY ARE CRAZY.

10:07.341 --> 10:09.140
YOU JUST DON'T KNOW.

10:09.142 --> 10:11.026
♪♪

10:12.846 --> 10:16.197
♪♪

10:23.557 --> 10:26.574
Tracie: IT WAS SATURDAY MORNING
WHEN CHRIS DIDN'T COME HOME,

10:26.576 --> 10:28.810
SO MY MOM CALLED
THE POLICE DEPARTMENT,

10:28.812 --> 10:30.395
AND THEY WERE
TELLING HER TO WAIT

10:30.397 --> 10:32.463
AND HE WOULD PROBABLY BE HOME.

10:32.465 --> 10:33.631
WELL, HE DIDN'T COME HOME,

10:33.633 --> 10:35.650
SO THEN SHE WENT
TO THE POLICE DEPARTMENT

10:35.652 --> 10:37.852
AND GOT THEM TO TAKE
A POLICE REPORT

10:37.854 --> 10:42.157
AND THEY WERE TELLING HER
THAT HE PROBABLY JUST RAN AWAY.

10:42.159 --> 10:43.908
Robb: THE POLICE DEPARTMENT
THOUGHT HE RAN AWAY

10:43.910 --> 10:46.528
BECAUSE HE LIKED TO GO
WITH HIS FRIENDS.

10:46.530 --> 10:49.614
HE WOULD SOMETIMES CHECK IN
WITH HIS MOM OR GRANDMOTHER,

10:49.616 --> 10:52.617
BUT SOMETIMES HE DIDN'T.

10:52.619 --> 10:54.619
YOU THINK HE'S JUST GOING OFF
BLOWING OFF SOME STEAM

10:54.621 --> 10:57.155
AND HE'S GOING TO
COME BACK HOME.

10:57.157 --> 10:59.457
Narrator: OTHER FRIENDS THINK
SOMETHING MORE COMPLICATED

10:59.459 --> 11:01.793
HAD BEEN GOING ON WITH CHRIS
EVER SINCE HE GOT

11:01.795 --> 11:04.929
KICKED OFF THE BASEBALL TEAM
FOUR MONTHS EARLIER.

11:06.466 --> 11:09.017
HE DIDN'T REALLY KNOW
HOW TO DEAL WITH IT.

11:09.019 --> 11:12.937
HE DIDN'T HAVE
THE BEST COPING SKILLS.

11:12.939 --> 11:14.606
HE SAID HE WAS
GOING TO RUN AWAY

11:14.608 --> 11:17.442
JUST BECAUSE SO MANY THINGS
WERE GOING ON.

11:21.347 --> 11:23.898
Narrator: BUT CHRIS' FAMILY
REFUSES TO BELIEVE

11:23.900 --> 11:26.735
HE WOULD LEAVE WITHOUT A WORD.

11:26.737 --> 11:29.988
THEY JUST TRULY ACTED
LIKE HE JUST RAN AWAY.

11:29.990 --> 11:32.440
AND LIKE I SAID,
HE WOULD NEVER RUN AWAY, NEVER.

11:32.442 --> 11:35.276
HE MIGHT GET MAD AND LEAVE
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS,

11:35.278 --> 11:36.911
BUT HE'D BE BACK.

11:36.913 --> 11:39.664
♪♪

11:42.202 --> 11:44.352
I WENT LOOKING
FOR CHRIS EVERYWHERE

11:44.354 --> 11:45.970
BECAUSE WHEN
HE DIDN'T COME HOME,

11:45.972 --> 11:47.389
I THOUGHT SOMETHING
HAPPENED TO HIM.

11:47.391 --> 11:49.474
HE COULD HAVE BEEN
HIT IN THE HEAD

11:49.476 --> 11:52.010
AND WAS LAYING IN A DITCH,
AND IT WAS COLD.

11:52.012 --> 11:55.213
I WENT AROUND TO THE CREEKS
AND PONDS AND DITCHES.

11:55.215 --> 11:57.232
I HAD POISON IVY ON ME.

11:57.234 --> 12:01.986
I MADE POSTERS AND PUT THEM UP
AT THE DIFFERENT STORES.

12:01.988 --> 12:03.238
Jen: I REMEMBER
MEETING UP WITH HER

12:03.240 --> 12:07.558
AND US GOING ALL OVER
THE PLACE HANGING POSTERS,

12:07.560 --> 12:09.944
FOR MISSING PERSON POSTERS.

12:09.946 --> 12:11.479
"HAVE YOU SEEN HIM?

12:11.481 --> 12:13.748
IF SO, PLEASE CALL US
AND LET US KNOW."

12:16.520 --> 12:18.887
A PART OF ME JUST FELT LIKE IT
WAS KIND OF --

12:18.889 --> 12:21.022
KIND OF A WASTE OF TIME,
YOU KNOW?

12:21.024 --> 12:23.074
I DIDN'T FEEL LIKE ANYTHING
BAD HAD HAPPENED TO HIM,

12:23.076 --> 12:24.342
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

12:24.344 --> 12:28.163
I FELT LIKE, UM...

12:28.165 --> 12:30.882
IN MY MIND, I WAS STILL HAVING
A LOT OF HOPE.

12:32.886 --> 12:35.303
♪♪

12:35.305 --> 12:37.255
Narrator: BUT THERE IS
ONE FAMILY MEMBER

12:37.257 --> 12:40.108
WHO MAY HAVE SPURRED CHRIS
TO LEAVE TOWN.

12:43.313 --> 12:45.429
Jen: I'D HAVE TO SAY
CHRIS AND MY DAD

12:45.431 --> 12:47.482
WERE PROBABLY THE CLOSEST.

12:47.484 --> 12:48.599
OUT OF ALL HIS KIDS,

12:48.601 --> 12:50.535
CHRIS PROBABLY LOVED HIM
THE MOST.

12:53.323 --> 12:57.942
Narrator: CHRIS' PARENTS
SEPARATE SOON AFTER HE'S BORN.

12:57.944 --> 13:01.212
Jen: CHRIS WANTED
THAT PERFECT STORY --

13:01.214 --> 13:03.665
THE HOUSE LIFE,
THE HOME LIFE YOU SEE ON TV,

13:03.667 --> 13:06.450
YOU KNOW, WHERE YOU HAVE A MOM
AND DAD THAT LOVE YOU.

13:06.452 --> 13:08.553
NO MATTER HOW MUCH HE WOULD SAY
IT DIDN'T BOTHER HIM,

13:08.555 --> 13:11.506
HE DIDN'T CARE,
HE'S HAPPY WHERE HE'S AT,

13:11.508 --> 13:14.726
HE'D DONE --
IT KILLED HIM INSIDE.

13:18.464 --> 13:20.932
Brittany: CHRIS' DAD
WAS IN PRISON

13:20.934 --> 13:23.184
FOR AN EXTENDED
PERIOD OF TIME,

13:23.186 --> 13:26.738
SO THAT BROUGHT A LOT
OF ANXIETIES FOR HIM.

13:26.740 --> 13:28.773
INMATE 46895.

13:28.775 --> 13:30.692
Jen: DRUGS.

13:30.694 --> 13:32.977
IT WAS ALWAYS DRUGS.

13:32.979 --> 13:37.648
HE WOULD GO TO PRISON,
HE WOULD BE THERE FOR YEARS.

13:37.650 --> 13:39.534
WHEN HE WOULD COME HOME
FROM PRISON,

13:39.536 --> 13:42.587
HE WAS JUST,
"OH, DADDY LOVES Y'ALL.

13:42.589 --> 13:44.172
I MISS Y'ALL SO MUCH,"
YOU KNOW?

13:44.174 --> 13:46.174
"I'M GOING TO DO THIS,
I'M GOING TO DO THAT."

13:46.176 --> 13:48.760
EMPTY PROMISES.

13:48.762 --> 13:52.180
AS SOON AS MY DAD GOT OUT
AND GOT BACK INTO THE LIFE,

13:52.182 --> 13:54.716
MY DAD WAS RIPPED OUT
OF CHRISTOPHER'S LIFE AGAIN.

13:54.718 --> 13:58.169
IT WAS JUST
A NEVER-ENDING CYCLE.

13:58.171 --> 14:00.805
THERE'S A THIN LINE
BETWEEN LOVE AND HATE.

14:00.807 --> 14:03.174
Narrator: JUST A FEW WEEKS
BEFORE CHRIS DISAPPEARED,

14:03.176 --> 14:04.893
HIS FATHER IS SCHEDULED
FOR RELEASE

14:04.895 --> 14:07.562
FROM A TEXAS
STATE PENITENTIARY.

14:07.564 --> 14:09.981
WHEN HE WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
GETTING OUT OF JAIL,

14:09.983 --> 14:11.199
THAT'S WHEN CHRIS WAS
TELLING ME,

14:11.201 --> 14:13.201
"DAD'S COMING HOME,
I DON'T WANT TO SEE HIM.

14:13.203 --> 14:16.520
YOU KNOW, I'M JUST TIRED
OF EVERYTHING."

14:16.522 --> 14:19.574
Narrator: MAYBE CHRIS RAN AWAY
TO AVOID SEEING HIS FATHER,

14:19.576 --> 14:22.961
BUT ACCORDING TO CHRIS' FAMILY,
AFTER HIS RELEASE,

14:22.963 --> 14:26.164
HIS DAD MOVES TO
ANOTHER TOWN IN TEXAS.

14:26.166 --> 14:29.500
♪♪

14:32.672 --> 14:34.538
AS THE DAYS MORPH INTO WEEKS,

14:34.540 --> 14:37.342
THE URGENCY
TO FIND CHRIS MOUNTS.

14:41.047 --> 14:43.064
Robb: DETECTIVES DID
EVERYTHING THEY COULD.

14:43.066 --> 14:45.483
THEY PUT FLYERS OUT,
THEY GOT DENTAL RECORDS,

14:45.485 --> 14:48.820
THEY OBVIOUSLY TALKED
TO THE FAMILY A LOT.

14:48.822 --> 14:50.772
THE KIDS AT SCHOOL,

14:50.774 --> 14:52.890
THEY HAD TO GO TALK TO
AND INTERVIEW.

14:52.892 --> 14:54.392
HOW LONG
HAVE YOU KNOWN HIM?

14:54.394 --> 14:56.694
HE WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL,
SO YOU COULD IMAGINE

14:56.696 --> 15:00.398
HOW MANY FRIENDS HE HAD
AND WHO HE HUNG OUT WITH.

15:00.400 --> 15:02.533
I MEAN,
I'D PROBABLY SAY HE'S...

15:02.535 --> 15:05.503
Brittany: SOME OF THE RUMORS
WERE THAT HE WENT TO MISSOURI,

15:05.505 --> 15:09.407
THAT HE MET SOMEBODY ONLINE.

15:09.409 --> 15:11.575
Tracie: ONE OF THEM
WAS THAT HE RAN AWAY

15:11.577 --> 15:13.845
WITH SOME OF HIS FRIENDS
TO GO TO OKLAHOMA.

15:13.847 --> 15:16.247
ANOTHER ONE WAS THAT
THERE WAS ANOTHER FRIEND

15:16.249 --> 15:20.134
THAT MOVED NORTH SOMEWHERE
AND THAT HE WAS WITH HIM.

15:20.136 --> 15:22.887
Brittany: ONE PERSON
TOLD ME THAT, NO,

15:22.889 --> 15:26.691
THAT HE HAD GOTTEN INTO IT
WITH SOME BAD GROUP OF PEOPLE

15:26.693 --> 15:30.395
OR WHATEVER IN OUR AREA
AND THEY HAD GOTTEN INTO IT

15:30.397 --> 15:33.698
AND SO THEY HAD TAKEN HIM.

15:33.700 --> 15:37.402
Samantha: EVERYTHING
GREW AND CHANGED

15:37.404 --> 15:39.120
AND THIS LITTLE BIT
WOULD GET THROWN IN HERE

15:39.122 --> 15:41.122
AND THAT LITTLE BIT WOULD
BE THROWN IN THERE,

15:41.124 --> 15:44.375
AND IT MAKES YOU CRAZY.

15:44.377 --> 15:46.878
IT -- IT MAKES YOU CRAZY.

15:49.115 --> 15:51.382
THEY FOLLOWED UP WITH LEADS
AND THEY TALKED TO EVERYBODY,

15:51.384 --> 15:53.251
BUT IT SEEMED LIKE IT
WAS GOING DOWN

15:53.253 --> 15:56.571
A LOT OF DIFFERENT RABBIT HOLES.

15:56.573 --> 15:59.240
Narrator: AS WEEKS PASS
WITH NO SIGN OF THE TEENAGER,

15:59.242 --> 16:04.412
CHRIS' FAMILY BELIEVES THERE'S
ONLY ONE EXPLANATION LEFT.

16:04.414 --> 16:06.797
Samantha: JUST THAT SOMEBODY
DID KILL HIM.

16:06.799 --> 16:11.569
THAT'S THE ONLY THING WHY
HE WOULDN'T HAVE COME HOME,

16:11.571 --> 16:15.606
AND THAT WAS ALWAYS IN MY MIND,
THAT SOMEBODY DID KILL HIM.

16:15.608 --> 16:16.807
THAT'S WHAT WE
COULDN'T FIGURE OUT.

16:16.809 --> 16:18.776
WHO WAS HIS ENEMY?

16:18.778 --> 16:21.279
WHO WOULD HAVE
WANTED HIM DEAD?

16:22.849 --> 16:25.817
♪♪

16:36.997 --> 16:39.030
Tracie: WE KEPT HIS
CHRISTMAS PRESENTS.

16:39.032 --> 16:42.116
WE PUT THEM IN A BOX
AND PUT THEM UP IN THE ATTIC,

16:42.118 --> 16:44.035
JUST THINKING, YOU KNOW,
IF HE EVER CAME HOME,

16:44.037 --> 16:45.953
WE COULD GIVE THEM TO HIM.

16:48.425 --> 16:50.591
IT WAS ROUGH.
I MEAN, GOSH.

16:50.593 --> 16:53.711
GRANDMA KEPT CHRIS' ROOM
JUST THE WAY IT WAS.

16:53.713 --> 16:54.962
I MEAN, FOR THE LONGEST,

16:54.964 --> 16:56.681
NO ONE WAS ALLOWED
TO GO IN THERE.

16:56.683 --> 16:58.132
"YOU BETTER NOT
WALK IN THAT ROOM,

16:58.134 --> 16:59.717
DON'T TOUCH HIS DOOR.

16:59.719 --> 17:01.019
JUST STAY OUT OF THERE.

17:01.021 --> 17:03.888
I WANT IT JUST LIKE HE LEFT IT
WHEN HE COMES HOME."

17:03.890 --> 17:07.291
♪♪

17:08.645 --> 17:10.311
Tracie: IT WAS REALLY HARD
FOR MY MOM

17:10.313 --> 17:12.647
BECAUSE SHE WAS
SO CLOSE TO CHRIS,

17:12.649 --> 17:16.401
AND IT TOOK A TOLL ON HER
AS FAR AS HER HEALTH, TOO.

17:16.403 --> 17:18.953
SHE DETERIORATED, YOU KNOW,
FROM THE WORRY

17:18.955 --> 17:24.375
AND CONSTANTLY LOOKING FOR HIM
AND JUST EVERYTHING SHE --

17:24.377 --> 17:27.328
THAT'S ALL SHE DID.

17:27.330 --> 17:29.697
Narrator: WHILE WANDA NEVER
STOPS HOPING HER GRANDSON

17:29.699 --> 17:31.215
WILL WALK THROUGH THE DOOR,

17:31.217 --> 17:35.470
CHRIS' MOM AND AUNT ARE
CONVINCED HE'S BEEN MURDERED.

17:35.472 --> 17:36.637
THAT'S WHAT WE
COULDN'T FIGURE OUT.

17:36.639 --> 17:37.839
WHO WAS HIS ENEMY?

17:40.093 --> 17:41.426
HE DIDN'T HAVE TOO MANY ENEMIES.

17:41.428 --> 17:42.877
LIKE, WHO WOULD
WANT HIM DEAD,

17:42.879 --> 17:46.431
OR WHO WOULD NOT
WANT HIM AROUND?

17:46.433 --> 17:48.182
MAYBE MY DAD
OWED SOMEBODY MONEY.

17:48.184 --> 17:50.568
SOMEBODY COULD HAVE TAKEN IT
OUT ON HIM, YOU KNOW,

17:50.570 --> 17:53.738
THROUGH THE DRUGS,
THROUGH THAT LIFESTYLE.

17:53.740 --> 17:56.941
MAYBE HE WAS TRYING TO DO
SOMETHING FOR MY DAD

17:56.943 --> 18:00.078
AND PAY OFF A DEBT
TO SAVE MY DAD'S LIFE.

18:01.948 --> 18:03.498
Zavala: YOU HAVE TO REMEMBER,

18:03.500 --> 18:06.367
MISSOURI CITY IS
VERY CLOSE TO HOUSTON.

18:06.369 --> 18:08.953
EVEN THOUGH IT'S SMALL-TOWN,
HAS THAT FEEL,

18:08.955 --> 18:12.573
MISSOURI CITY IS NOT
VOID OF GANGS,

18:12.575 --> 18:16.043
NOT VOID OF DRUGS,
JUST LIKE ANY OTHER BIG CITY.

18:18.631 --> 18:19.914
LOOK WHO'S COMING.

18:19.916 --> 18:21.716
Tracie: WHEN POLICE WERE
GOING THROUGH THE COMPUTER,

18:21.718 --> 18:23.718
THEY FOUND SOMETHING
ABOUT A GANG

18:23.720 --> 18:27.105
IN THE AREA BY THE SCHOOL.

18:29.476 --> 18:30.858
I TALKED TO
SOME OF HIS FRIENDS.

18:30.860 --> 18:33.227
HIS FRIENDS SAID THAT, WELL,
HE HAD SAID SOMETHING TO,

18:33.229 --> 18:35.029
LIKE, THE LEADER OF IT.

18:37.233 --> 18:39.951
Samantha: HE SAID WHAT
WAS ON HIS MIND

18:39.953 --> 18:42.570
AND HAD A TEMPER.

18:42.572 --> 18:45.790
HE WOULD DEFINITELY LET YOU KNOW
WHEN HE WAS MAD.

18:45.792 --> 18:48.826
♪♪

18:51.414 --> 18:53.414
Narrator: SO FAR,
THERE'S NO EVIDENCE

18:53.416 --> 18:57.718
TO SUPPORT ANY THEORIES
ABOUT POTENTIAL ENEMIES,

18:57.720 --> 19:01.172
BUT CHRIS' STATE OF MIND
ON THE MORNING HE WENT MISSING

19:01.174 --> 19:05.259
SUGGESTS ANOTHER
TRAGIC EXPLANATION.

19:05.261 --> 19:07.562
THERE WERE A COUPLE
OF CONVERSATIONS

19:07.564 --> 19:10.148
WHERE CHRIS HAD TALKED ABOUT,
YOU KNOW,

19:10.150 --> 19:15.236
THE IDEA OF NOT
WAKING UP AGAIN OR, UM,

19:15.238 --> 19:18.656
JUST DISAPPEARING,
NOT WANTING TO BE HERE ANYMORE.

19:22.645 --> 19:25.530
BECAUSE HE LOST SUCH
A LARGE PART OF HIS IDENTITY

19:25.532 --> 19:29.000
WHEN HE GOT KICKED OFF
THE BASEBALL TEAM,

19:29.002 --> 19:31.869
YOU KNOW, THERE WERE SOME
REALLY INTENSE TIMES

19:31.871 --> 19:35.289
WHERE HE WAS SUICIDAL.

19:35.291 --> 19:37.041
Zavala: ON PAPER,
IT MADE SENSE THAT

19:37.043 --> 19:38.709
HE HAD IT IN HIM
TO HURT HIMSELF.

19:38.711 --> 19:41.429
DIDN'T MAKE SENSE TO MOM,
BECAUSE AS A PARENT,

19:41.431 --> 19:42.597
YOU DON'T WANT
TO THINK THAT, RIGHT?

19:42.599 --> 19:43.965
YOU WANT TO FIND YOUR KID.

19:43.967 --> 19:47.334
YOU DON'T WANT THAT
AS YOUR FINAL ANSWER.

19:47.336 --> 19:50.438
I WOULD SIT AT WORK,
AND IN THE DOWNTIME,

19:50.440 --> 19:53.457
I WOULD GO ON
THE MISSING PERSONS WEB SITES

19:53.459 --> 19:56.961
AND I WOULD LOOK FOR
THE UNIDENTIFIED BODIES

19:56.963 --> 19:59.614
AND SEE IF ANY OF THEM
COULD BE HIM.

19:59.616 --> 20:00.848
WERE THEY IN
THE RIGHT AGE RANGE?

20:00.850 --> 20:01.849
WERE THEY MALE?

20:01.851 --> 20:03.484
WHAT DATE DID THEY GO MISSING?

20:06.206 --> 20:10.808
UNTIL YOU ACTUALLY HAVE
THAT BODY AND ACTUALLY KNOW,

20:10.810 --> 20:13.127
YOU NEVER LOSE HOPE.

20:13.129 --> 20:14.996
YOU NEVER LOSE HOPE.

20:14.998 --> 20:18.382
♪♪

20:26.226 --> 20:29.393
MISSOURI CITY FINALLY SAID
THAT THERE WAS TOO MUCH --

20:29.395 --> 20:30.678
TOO MANY DIFFERENT STORIES.

20:30.680 --> 20:33.397
THEY COULDN'T
CONFIRM ANYTHING.

20:33.399 --> 20:37.735
SO THEY BASICALLY TURNED IT
INTO A COLD CASE FILE

20:37.737 --> 20:41.355
AND THEY JUST STOPPED TRYING
TO DO ANYTHING WITH IT.

20:46.412 --> 20:48.279
YOU WORK IT FOR SO LONG

20:48.281 --> 20:49.730
AND THERE'S NOTHING ELSE
YOU CAN DO.

20:49.732 --> 20:53.400
IF YOU HAVE NOTHING,
YOU HAVE NOTHING.

20:53.402 --> 20:56.621
WHERE DO YOU GO?
WHAT DO YOU DO?

20:56.623 --> 20:59.790
♪♪

21:01.544 --> 21:05.746
HIS FAVORITE COLOR WAS BLUE,
AND MY MOM COLLECTED BLUE VASES

21:05.748 --> 21:08.599
AND THINGS AND PUT IT
AROUND HIS PICTURE.

21:08.601 --> 21:10.551
I LIKE THE ANGELS,

21:10.553 --> 21:13.387
LIKE GUARDIAN ANGELS
WATCHING OVER CHRIS.

21:13.389 --> 21:15.139
I FELT BAD FOR MY SISTER
WITH ALL THIS,

21:15.141 --> 21:16.440
BECAUSE, I MEAN,
THAT'S HER SON.

21:16.442 --> 21:19.143
THAT WAS HER FIRSTBORN.

21:19.145 --> 21:22.096
IT'S UNREAL,
THE ROLLER COASTER OF EMOTIONS

21:22.098 --> 21:25.599
THAT WE HAD TO ENDURE
DURING THIS.

21:25.601 --> 21:28.452
Tracie: IN HIS WORK GLOVES
AND NOT BASEBALL GLOVES.

21:28.454 --> 21:31.872
ALWAYS WANTED TO BE DIFFERENT,
SETTING TRENDS.

21:31.874 --> 21:34.408
HE SAID HE COULD GET
A BETTER GRIP ON THE BAT.

21:34.410 --> 21:35.626
Samantha:
MENTALLY AND PHYSICALLY,

21:35.628 --> 21:39.997
IT TOOK A TOLL ON HER,
AND SHE CHANGED.

21:39.999 --> 21:42.083
HONESTLY,
I THINK IT CHANGED US ALL.

21:42.085 --> 21:44.919
♪♪

21:47.140 --> 21:49.256
Tracie: WE EVEN
WENT TO PSYCHICS.

21:49.258 --> 21:51.008
I REALLY DIDN'T
BELIEVE IN PSYCHICS,

21:51.010 --> 21:54.395
BUT I WOULD TRY ANYTHING
TO FIND MY SON.

21:54.397 --> 21:58.149
♪♪

22:01.571 --> 22:07.241
SHE TOLD US SOME
REALLY INTERESTING THINGS,

22:07.243 --> 22:09.143
WHERE CHRIS WAS WITH
THREE GUYS.

22:09.145 --> 22:12.997
THEY WENT DOWN
A LONG DIRT ROAD.

22:12.999 --> 22:13.998
THERE WERE NO LIGHTS.

22:14.000 --> 22:15.766
THERE WAS A TREE LINE.

22:15.768 --> 22:17.201
THERE WAS AN ALTERCATION.

22:17.203 --> 22:20.204
CHRIS WAS SHOT
IN THE HEAD.

22:24.210 --> 22:27.094
I ASKED THE LADY,
I SAID, "WHERE IS HE?"

22:27.096 --> 22:29.096
AND SHE ACTUALLY
DREW US A MAP.

22:29.098 --> 22:32.350
SHE DREW A PICTURE OF A FENCE,
AND THE TREE WAS THERE

22:32.352 --> 22:36.003
AND HOW THE TREE AND FENCE GREW,
YOU KNOW, INTO IT,

22:36.005 --> 22:38.689
AND IT HAD BEEN THERE
FOR A LONG TIME

22:38.691 --> 22:40.558
AND IT WAS A LOW AREA

22:40.560 --> 22:43.027
AND IT WAS LIKE
WATER WOULD RUN THROUGH,

22:43.029 --> 22:47.531
AND SHE DREW PICTURES OF WHEELS
AND RIMS ON THE VEHICLE.

22:47.533 --> 22:50.451
♪♪

22:52.955 --> 22:54.688
Samantha: I TOOK OFF
WORK ONE DAY WITH TRACIE

22:54.690 --> 22:58.492
AND WE WERE GOING DOWN
FENCE LINES AND WHATEVER.

22:58.494 --> 23:02.463
WE FOUND SOME BONES,
CALLED THE POLICE.

23:02.465 --> 23:03.464
IT WASN'T HIS.

23:03.466 --> 23:05.332
THEY WERE ANIMAL BONES.

23:05.334 --> 23:08.419
♪♪

23:17.230 --> 23:21.065
AND MOM KEPT GOING TO
THE POLICE STATION AND SAYING,

23:21.067 --> 23:26.337
"PLEASE, FIND OUT WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY GRANDSON BEFORE I DIE.

23:26.339 --> 23:29.407
I NEED TO KNOW BEFORE I DIE."

23:29.409 --> 23:32.660
Narrator: BUT CHRIS' MOM IS
ABOUT TO UNCOVER A NEW LEAD

23:32.662 --> 23:36.730
FROM SOMEONE WHO WAS TOO AFRAID
TO SPEAK UP BEFORE.

23:36.732 --> 23:39.033
SHE SAID THAT SHE HAD
HEARD SOMETHING

23:39.035 --> 23:41.235
AND THAT SHE KNEW SOMETHING.

23:41.237 --> 23:43.170
Robb: THIS IS IT.

23:43.172 --> 23:45.072
WE'VE -- WE'VE DONE IT.

23:45.074 --> 23:46.874
THIS IS SOMETHING BIG.

23:48.494 --> 23:51.462
♪♪

23:55.001 --> 23:56.934
Tracie: I LOOKED AT THE CARS
WHEN THEY DROVE BY.

23:56.936 --> 23:58.669
I DID.

23:58.671 --> 24:02.706
WE'D SIT WITH THE FRONT DOOR
OPEN AND WATCH OUTSIDE, TOO.

24:02.708 --> 24:04.375
YOU'RE CONSTANTLY
LOOKING FOR HIM

24:04.377 --> 24:06.644
AND IT'S LIKE YOUR LIFE
STANDS STILL.

24:06.646 --> 24:10.397
ALL YOU THINK ABOUT DAY
AND NIGHT IS, "WHERE IS HE?

24:10.399 --> 24:13.384
IS HE OKAY?
WHERE DO I LOOK NOW?"

24:13.386 --> 24:16.687
♪♪

24:21.360 --> 24:24.278
I MADE A PROMISE THAT I
DIDN'T CARE HOW LONG IT TOOK

24:24.280 --> 24:28.649
OR WHATEVER I HAD TO DO,
THAT I WAS GOING TO FIND HIM.

24:28.651 --> 24:30.367
Narrator: LIVING WITH
THE CONSTANT FEAR

24:30.369 --> 24:32.486
OF WHAT MAY HAVE HAPPENED
TO HER SON,

24:32.488 --> 24:37.708
TRACIE OPENS HER HOME
TO OTHER TEENAGERS IN DISTRESS.

24:37.710 --> 24:39.043
Tracie: A LOT OF THE KIDS
WOULD RUN AWAY,

24:39.045 --> 24:40.377
AND I WAS SCARED THAT SOMETHING

24:40.379 --> 24:42.379
WOULD HAPPEN TO THEM
ON THE STREETS,

24:42.381 --> 24:44.665
SO I WOULD LET THEM
COME AND LIVE WITH ME

24:44.667 --> 24:47.834
AND I WOULD TAKE CARE OF THEM
AND HELP THEM.

24:47.836 --> 24:51.004
Narrator: IN THE FALL OF 2007,
FIVE YEARS AFTER

24:51.006 --> 24:54.841
HER SON'S DISAPPEARANCE,
TRACIE TAKES IN JOSH FRETZ,

24:54.843 --> 24:59.613
A TROUBLED TEEN A FEW YEARS
BEHIND CHRIS IN SCHOOL.

24:59.615 --> 25:01.782
I REALLY DIDN'T
KNOW HIM THAT WELL.

25:01.784 --> 25:05.035
HE STAYED MAYBE A WEEK
AND A HALF.

25:05.037 --> 25:08.205
AND THEN ONE DAY HE SAW
A PICTURE OF CHRIS.

25:08.207 --> 25:10.824
♪♪

25:12.695 --> 25:15.913
AND I THINK THAT'S
WHEN HE TOOK OFF.

25:20.202 --> 25:21.919
Tracie: AND I WENT AND SPOKE
TO JOSH'S MOTHER

25:21.921 --> 25:23.870
BECAUSE I WAS WORRIED ABOUT HIM,

25:23.872 --> 25:26.223
AND SHE TOLD ME THAT
SOMETHING HAPPENED TO HIM

25:26.225 --> 25:32.062
WHEN HE WAS 13 YEARS OLD
AND HE WON'T TALK ABOUT IT.

25:32.064 --> 25:36.183
Narrator: TRACIE SENSES JOSH
KNOWS SOMETHING ABOUT CHRIS,

25:36.185 --> 25:38.885
BUT SHE NEVER
SEES HIM AGAIN.

25:38.887 --> 25:41.805
♪♪

25:45.111 --> 25:48.329
MORE YEARS PASS,
BUT CHRIS' MOM REFUSES

25:48.331 --> 25:50.497
TO GIVE UP SEARCHING
FOR HER SON.

25:50.499 --> 25:53.701
♪♪

25:56.789 --> 25:58.872
I TOOK A JOB AT A BAR.

25:58.874 --> 26:01.258
IT WAS CLOSE BY THE HOUSE
BECAUSE THE KIDS

26:01.260 --> 26:03.594
WERE OLD ENOUGH TO DRINK,
AND I THOUGHT,

26:03.596 --> 26:08.132
"WELL, SOMEBODY MIGHT GET DRUNK,
SLIP UP, SAY SOMETHING."

26:10.553 --> 26:13.053
HOW ARE YOU TWO DOING?
GOOD.

26:13.055 --> 26:14.939
Samantha: SHE WOULD
MINGLE WITH THE KIDS

26:14.941 --> 26:17.107
AND TRY TO MAKE FRIENDS
WITH THOSE KIDS

26:17.109 --> 26:20.728
TO SEE ANYTHING AND EVERYTHING
THAT SHE COULD FIND OUT.

26:20.730 --> 26:23.364
WHERE ARE YOU GUYS FROM?

26:23.366 --> 26:24.782
FROM AROUND HERE.

26:24.784 --> 26:26.266
BOTH OF US,
BORN AND RAISED.

26:26.268 --> 26:28.935
Tracie: EVERY TIME SOMEONE
WOULD COME IN FROM THE SCHOOL,

26:28.937 --> 26:30.270
I'D SAY, "OH,
DO YOU REMEMBER CHRIS DAIGLE?"

26:30.272 --> 26:33.457
AND ONE DAY ONE OF THE GIRLS
FROM SCHOOL CAME IN

26:33.459 --> 26:36.710
AND SHE SAID THAT
SHE HAD HEARD SOMETHING,

26:36.712 --> 26:39.463
BUT SHE DIDN'T WANT TO TELL ME
ANYTHING ABOUT IT,

26:39.465 --> 26:42.383
JUST THAT SHE KNEW SOMETHING.

26:45.171 --> 26:47.388
I'M GOING TO GIVE YOU
A PHONE NUMBER.

26:47.390 --> 26:49.506
SO I GAVE HER
THE DETECTIVE'S INFORMATION

26:49.508 --> 26:52.309
AND SHE SAID THAT SHE WOULD
TALK TO THE DETECTIVE,

26:52.311 --> 26:56.113
AND I FELT THAT MAYBE
SOMETHING COULD COME OF IT.

26:56.115 --> 26:59.450
♪♪

27:02.321 --> 27:04.905
Narrator: THE YOUNG WOMAN GOES
DOWN TO THE POLICE STATION

27:04.907 --> 27:07.408
AND TELLS DETECTIVES
WHAT SHE KNOWS,

27:07.410 --> 27:09.943
STARTING WITH THE CONVERSATION
SHE HAD WITH ONE OF

27:09.945 --> 27:12.496
CHRIS' GOOD FRIENDS,
RICKY MENDOZA,

27:12.498 --> 27:16.149
TWO MONTHS AFTER
CHRIS DISAPPEARED.

27:16.151 --> 27:19.670
SHE SAID THAT SHE WAS IN THE CAR
WITH RICKY MENDOZA.

27:22.541 --> 27:25.292
AND THEY GOT ON
THE SUBJECT ABOUT CHRIS.

27:27.880 --> 27:31.382
AND HE SAID THAT
HE KILLED CHRIS,

27:31.384 --> 27:33.584
AND SHE'S LIKE,
"NO, YOU DIDN'T.

27:33.586 --> 27:34.752
THERE'S NO WAY."

27:34.754 --> 27:38.622
HE'S LIKE, "YEAH,
I'LL SHOW YOU WHERE HIS BODY IS.

27:38.624 --> 27:41.642
I'LL SHOW YOU."

27:41.644 --> 27:44.395
SO HE DROVE DOWN
TO THIS FIELD AND HE POINTED.

27:44.397 --> 27:46.146
HE SAID,
"IT'S RIGHT OVER THERE."

27:50.653 --> 27:52.119
Narrator: ACCORDING
TO THE WOMAN,

27:52.121 --> 27:54.371
THE FIELD THAT RICKY
HAD TAKEN HER TO

27:54.373 --> 27:56.623
IS IN NEARBY
FORT BEND COUNTY,

27:56.625 --> 28:00.544
BUT AFTER AN EXHAUSTIVE SEARCH,
POLICE COME UP EMPTY-HANDED.

28:02.581 --> 28:05.416
Tracie: NOTHING REALLY
CAME OUT OF IT AFTER THAT.

28:05.418 --> 28:07.501
WE FELT LIKE IT WAS
ANOTHER RABBIT HOLE.

28:07.503 --> 28:10.871
THEY DIDN'T HAVE
ANY PROOF OF ANYTHING.

28:10.873 --> 28:13.173
Narrator: WITH NO EVIDENCE
OR TESTIMONY TO SUPPORT

28:13.175 --> 28:16.393
THE WOMAN'S STRANGE STORY
ABOUT CHRIS' FRIEND RICKY,

28:16.395 --> 28:18.846
THE CASE CONTINUES
TO LANGUISH.

28:18.848 --> 28:21.765
♪♪

28:25.154 --> 28:28.188
Narrator: A YEAR LATER,
IN THE SUMMER OF 2010,

28:28.190 --> 28:29.823
A NEW DETECTIVE IS ASSIGNED

28:29.825 --> 28:32.242
TO LOOK AT THE DEPARTMENT'S
COLD CASES.

28:34.530 --> 28:37.247
WHAT I LIKED ABOUT COLD CASES,
NUMBER ONE,

28:37.249 --> 28:39.616
IS BRINGING CLOSURE
TO FAMILY.

28:39.618 --> 28:43.087
I COULDN'T IMAGINE
THE WONDERING,

28:43.089 --> 28:45.238
"WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY LOVED ONE?"

28:45.240 --> 28:48.792
THIS ONE INTRIGUED ME BECAUSE
THERE WERE SOME LEADS IN IT

28:48.794 --> 28:51.411
WHERE IT JUST SEEMED LIKE
IT JUST DROPPED OFF

28:51.413 --> 28:53.914
AND IT WASN'T FOLLOWED UP.

28:53.916 --> 28:57.551
THERE WAS A STATEMENT
FROM A FEMALE.

28:57.553 --> 28:59.603
SHE SAID THAT SHE WAS
WITH RICKY MENDOZA

28:59.605 --> 29:03.223
AND HE WAS BRAGGING THAT
HE DID SOMETHING TO CHRIS.

29:06.595 --> 29:09.563
Narrator: DETECTIVE ROBB DECIDES
THE FIELD THE WOMAN IDENTIFIED

29:09.565 --> 29:14.701
IN FORT BEND COUNTY
DESERVES A SECOND LOOK.

29:14.703 --> 29:17.454
Robb: SO WE CALLED THE TEXAS
DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS

29:17.456 --> 29:19.773
AND THEY BROUGHT
SOME CADAVER DOGS DOWN

29:19.775 --> 29:25.462
AND WE RAN TWO DOGS,
AND THEY HAD HITS.

29:25.464 --> 29:27.080
I THOUGHT WE HAD SOMETHING.

29:27.082 --> 29:30.167
I THOUGHT, "OH, MY GOSH.
CHRIS IS BURIED HERE."

29:34.640 --> 29:40.227
WE CLEARED OUT THIS HUGE AREA,
START DIGGING UP THE GROUND.

29:40.229 --> 29:42.229
EVERYBODY WAS EXHAUSTED.

29:46.301 --> 29:48.185
AND THEN ALL THE HOPES
STARTED TO DETERIORATE

29:48.187 --> 29:50.771
BECAUSE WE WEREN'T
FINDING ANYTHING.

29:50.773 --> 29:53.907
YOU KNOW, YOUR HOPES GO ON
A ROLLER COASTER FROM,

29:53.909 --> 29:56.977
"THIS IS IT,
WE'RE GOING TO FIND CHRIS,"

29:56.979 --> 30:01.431
TO, "WHAT ARE WE
GOING TO DO NOW?"

30:01.433 --> 30:04.067
WHEN WE WENT TO THE FIELD
AND WE DIDN'T FIND ANYTHING,

30:04.069 --> 30:07.054
WE KNEW WE HAD TO START
GOING TO TALK TO SOME PEOPLE.

30:07.056 --> 30:08.922
I FIGURED AFTER TIME EXPIRED,

30:08.924 --> 30:13.460
THAT SOMEBODY WOULD BE
EVENTUALLY WILLING TO TALK.

30:13.462 --> 30:18.549
SO WE TRACKED DOWN
ONE OF HIS BUDDIES, JOSHUA.

30:18.551 --> 30:20.350
Narrator: NOW IN HIS EARLY 20s,

30:20.352 --> 30:22.886
JOSH FRETZ WAS ONE OF
CHRIS' MANY FRIENDS

30:22.888 --> 30:27.173
QUESTIONED DURING
THE INITIAL INVESTIGATION.

30:27.175 --> 30:29.175
Robb: WE FOUND OUT
WHERE HE WORKED

30:29.177 --> 30:32.613
AND WE WENT DOWN
TO HIS JOB IN HOUSTON

30:32.615 --> 30:34.481
AND I TALKED TO HIS BOSS.

30:34.483 --> 30:35.949
Man: HEY, JOSH.

30:35.951 --> 30:37.985
THERE ARE A COUPLE OF GUYS OUT
HERE THAT NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

30:37.987 --> 30:39.286
OKAY.

30:39.288 --> 30:42.322
♪♪

30:45.193 --> 30:47.411
Narrator: JOSH FRETZ
IS ALSO THE TROUBLED KID

30:47.413 --> 30:50.163
WHO BRIEFLY STAYED
WITH CHRIS' MOTHER.

30:52.918 --> 30:54.551
Robb: SO JOSHUA COMES IN

30:54.553 --> 30:57.638
AND I INTRODUCE MYSELF
AND MY PARTNER TO HIM.

30:57.640 --> 30:59.523
WE SIT DOWN AT THIS
CONFERENCE TABLE,

30:59.525 --> 31:01.258
AND I'M STARTING ALREADY
TO GET A LITTLE VIBE

31:01.260 --> 31:04.210
THAT SOMETHING'S GOING ON.

31:04.212 --> 31:06.713
JOSH WAS NERVOUS,
JOSH WAS SCARED.

31:06.715 --> 31:08.649
DEER IN THE HEADLIGHTS LOOK.

31:08.651 --> 31:10.551
A LITTLE FLUSHED.

31:10.553 --> 31:13.854
ANTSY A LITTLE BIT.

31:13.856 --> 31:16.323
WE EXPLAINED
WHY WE WERE THERE.

31:16.325 --> 31:21.078
I SAID, "YEARS HAVE GONE BY,
AND HOW WOULD YOUR FAMILY FEEL

31:21.080 --> 31:23.597
IF THEY HAD NO IDEA
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?"

31:23.599 --> 31:27.784
HIS EYES STARTED WATERING
A LITTLE BIT.

31:27.786 --> 31:31.922
JOSHUA ASKED ME, HE GOES,
"AM I GOING TO GET IN TROUBLE?"

31:31.924 --> 31:34.041
I SAID, "IT DEPENDS.
DID YOU KILL CHRIS?"

31:35.794 --> 31:39.546
♪♪

31:50.342 --> 31:54.645
Robb: JOSHUA ASKED ME, HE GOES,
"AM I GOING TO GET IN TROUBLE?"

31:54.647 --> 31:57.681
I SAID, "IT DEPENDS.
DID YOU KILL CHRIS?"

31:57.683 --> 32:00.017
AND HE SAID, "NO."

32:00.019 --> 32:02.819
AND I SAID, "OKAY, THEN YOU'RE
NOT GOING TO GET IN TROUBLE."

32:02.821 --> 32:07.941
SO JOSHUA TELLS ME THE STORY
ABOUT RICKY MENDOZA

32:07.943 --> 32:10.661
AND THE JEALOUSY
THAT HE HAD TOWARDS CHRIS.

32:10.663 --> 32:12.796
HEADS UP.

32:12.798 --> 32:15.215
Narrator: THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
IN ALL THESE YEARS

32:15.217 --> 32:20.286
THAT POLICE LEARN RICKY
HAD A PROBLEM WITH CHRIS.

32:20.288 --> 32:23.123
Brittany: RICKY AND CHRIS
PLAYED BASEBALL TOGETHER.

32:23.125 --> 32:24.124
THEY WERE FRIENDS...

32:24.126 --> 32:25.475
READY FOR THIS,
RICKY?

32:25.477 --> 32:27.344
TWO VERY DIFFERENT PEOPLE.

32:27.346 --> 32:30.480
CHRIS WAS VERY LOUD,
COULD TALK TO ANYBODY,

32:30.482 --> 32:34.401
WAS GOOFY, YOU KNOW,
LAUGHED A LOT,

32:34.403 --> 32:36.353
AND RICKY WAS VERY STOIC.

32:36.355 --> 32:39.022
JUST THROW THE BALL.

32:39.024 --> 32:40.490
Jen: RICKY ALWAYS STOOD
IN HIS SHADOW.

32:40.492 --> 32:43.476
HE WASN'T THE ALL-STAR PLAYER
THAT CHRIS WAS, YOU KNOW?

32:43.478 --> 32:47.748
CHRIS HAD ALL THE FRIENDS,
CHRIS WAS MR. POPULAR.

32:47.750 --> 32:49.082
RICKY DIDN'T GET
SO MANY INVITES.

32:49.084 --> 32:51.317
YOU KNOW, HE WAS KIND OF
THE CHUBBY KID

32:51.319 --> 32:55.455
WITH BAD ACNE, YOU KNOW?

32:55.457 --> 32:58.041
ONLY THING HE HAD
WAS A CUTE GIRLFRIEND.

33:01.797 --> 33:07.333
Robb: JOSH SAID THAT
RICKY SAW CHRIS IN SCHOOL,

33:07.335 --> 33:08.552
AND CHRIS WAS IN A CLASSROOM,

33:08.554 --> 33:10.020
AND HE WAS MESSING AROUND

33:10.022 --> 33:12.439
OR FLIRTING WITH RICKY'S
GIRLFRIEND AT THE TIME.

33:14.727 --> 33:17.310
Brittany: IT MADE SENSE BECAUSE
CHRIS WAS A BIG FLIRT,

33:17.312 --> 33:20.680
BUT AT THE SAME TIME,
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN A JOKE

33:20.682 --> 33:23.984
OR IT WOULD HAVE BEEN SILLY.

33:23.986 --> 33:27.654
Jen: FROM THE STORIES,
RICKY WAS VERY OVERPROTECTIVE,

33:27.656 --> 33:29.623
YOU KNOW,
"I'M YOUR BOYFRIEND.

33:29.625 --> 33:32.542
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO
TALK TO OTHER GUYS."

33:32.544 --> 33:35.345
Brittany: I THINK THAT CHRIS
HAD THE PERSONALITY

33:35.347 --> 33:37.363
THAT RICKY WANTED TO HAVE.

33:37.365 --> 33:39.633
I THINK IT RAN ON
A MUCH DEEPER LEVEL

33:39.635 --> 33:42.886
THAN JUST
FIGHTING OVER A GIRL.

33:45.641 --> 33:47.457
Narrator: ACCORDING TO JOSH,

33:47.459 --> 33:50.160
ON THE AFTERNOON
OF NOVEMBER 7, 2002,

33:50.162 --> 33:53.897
RICKY DECIDES
TO GET HIS REVENGE.

33:53.899 --> 33:57.234
Robb: RICKY WENT TO
A HOUSE THAT CHRIS WAS AT,

33:57.236 --> 33:59.186
GOT HIM IN THE TRUCK,

33:59.188 --> 34:03.106
GOT JOSH
AND ANOTHER INDIVIDUAL,

34:03.108 --> 34:05.409
AND SAID,
"LET'S GO PICK SOME MUSHROOMS."

34:05.411 --> 34:08.445
♪♪

34:21.576 --> 34:23.576
LET'S GO.

34:23.578 --> 34:26.346
♪♪

34:28.267 --> 34:33.520
AND THEY WENT OUT TO THIS FIELD
AND PARKED THE TRUCK.

34:33.522 --> 34:36.773
♪♪

34:47.286 --> 34:49.069
THEY HOPPED THE FENCE,
HE SAID.

34:49.071 --> 34:51.621
HE SAID THEY WALKED
AROUND THIS PASTURE.

34:53.942 --> 34:57.077
[ THUNDER ]

34:59.631 --> 35:02.749
JOSH SAID THEY WERE ALL LOOKING
ON THE GROUND FOR 'SHROOMS

35:02.751 --> 35:05.469
AND RICKY HAD
HIS SHOTGUN WITH HIM.

35:05.471 --> 35:08.388
♪♪

35:10.225 --> 35:13.093
AND HE SAID HE LOOKED UP
AND HE SAW RICKY POINT IT

35:13.095 --> 35:14.845
AT THE BACK OF CHRIS' HEAD.

35:17.683 --> 35:20.233
[ GUNSHOT ]

35:20.235 --> 35:22.135
RICKY PULLED THE TRIGGER.

35:22.137 --> 35:25.322
♪♪

35:30.195 --> 35:33.430
HE SAID HE SAW CHRIS' EYES
ROLL IN THE BACK OF HIS HEAD...

35:36.435 --> 35:37.667
AND HE SAW BLOOD,

35:37.669 --> 35:41.238
AND THEN CHRIS WAS JUST
MOTIONLESS ON THE GROUND.

35:41.240 --> 35:42.439
HE SAID,
"WE WERE FREAKING OUT.

35:42.441 --> 35:45.041
WE JUST STARTED RUNNING
BACK TO THE TRUCK."

35:45.043 --> 35:48.962
AND WHEN HE SAID THAT
SO DESCRIPTIVE BACK THEN,

35:48.964 --> 35:51.831
I KNEW HE WAS
TELLING THE TRUTH.

35:51.833 --> 35:54.267
Narrator: JOSH'S STORY
IS UNCANNILY SIMILAR

35:54.269 --> 35:57.304
TO THE ACCOUNT OF CHRIS' DEATH
GIVEN TO HIS FAMILY

35:57.306 --> 36:00.724
BY A PSYCHIC
EIGHT YEARS EARLIER.

36:00.726 --> 36:04.227
POLICE TRACK DOWN THE OTHER
TEENAGER IN THE CAR THAT DAY,

36:04.229 --> 36:06.062
DAVID GARCIA.

36:08.233 --> 36:09.983
WE JUST NEED TO HEAR IT
FROM YOU NOW.

36:09.985 --> 36:11.234
HE'S NERVOUS.

36:11.236 --> 36:13.737
I WAS LIKE,
"WHAT HAPPENED TO CHRIS?"

36:13.739 --> 36:15.121
AND I WAS LIKE,
"YOU NEED TO TELL ME THE TRUTH,

36:15.123 --> 36:16.873
BECAUSE I ALREADY KNOW."

36:16.875 --> 36:18.658
OKAY.

36:18.660 --> 36:21.361
SO HE TELLS
THE SAME STORY.

36:21.363 --> 36:22.879
Narrator: AT THE END
OF THE INTERVIEW,

36:22.881 --> 36:26.466
DAVID GIVES DETECTIVES
DIRECTIONS TO A WOODED AREA

36:26.468 --> 36:28.585
NEAR THE FIELD
WHERE RICKY HAD FORCED THEM

36:28.587 --> 36:30.921
TO HELP HIDE CHRIS' BODY.

36:30.923 --> 36:33.473
THE FIELD IS JUST 1,500 FEET

36:33.475 --> 36:37.978
FROM WHERE THE GIRL HAD
TAKEN THEM TWO YEARS EARLIER.

36:37.980 --> 36:39.429
Robb: SO WE'RE WALKING AROUND

36:39.431 --> 36:42.399
AND SERGEANT McKINNON
LOOKS DOWN ON THE GROUND

36:42.401 --> 36:44.434
AND HE SEES
WHAT APPEARS TO BE A BONE

36:44.436 --> 36:47.571
STICKING OUT OF THE GROUND.

36:47.573 --> 36:51.241
HE WAS LIKE,
"THAT LOOKS HUMAN TO ME."

36:51.243 --> 36:54.060
Narrator: DNA ANALYSIS
CONFIRMS THE BONE

36:54.062 --> 36:56.162
BELONGS TO
CHRISTOPHER DAIGLE.

36:56.164 --> 36:59.349
WE FOUND BONES,
A FEW BONES.

36:59.351 --> 37:02.068
WE DIDN'T FIND ALL OF CHRIS.

37:02.070 --> 37:04.788
Narrator: AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,
DETECTIVES ASSUME

37:04.790 --> 37:07.424
ANIMALS SPREAD
THE REST OF HIS REMAINS.

37:07.426 --> 37:10.760
♪♪

37:12.464 --> 37:14.931
Samantha: I THINK IT WAS
IN EARLY TO MID-AUGUST,

37:14.933 --> 37:19.236
MY SISTER CALLED ME AND SAID,
"SAMANTHA,

37:19.238 --> 37:20.737
THEY FOUND CHRIS."

37:20.739 --> 37:22.222
AND I, "WHAT?"

37:22.224 --> 37:24.024
IT'S GIVING ME CHILLS NOW.

37:26.261 --> 37:29.462
SHE SAID, "THEY'RE ARRESTING
RICKY MENDOZA TODAY."

37:29.464 --> 37:31.982
WE JUST BOTH
BROKE DOWN AND CRIED.

37:31.984 --> 37:34.100
FINALLY,
WE'RE GETTING THERE.

37:34.102 --> 37:38.604
IT FELT LIKE, "OKAY, FINALLY,
SOMETHING HAS HAPPENED."

37:38.606 --> 37:40.957
Samantha: IT WAS FINALLY OVER,
AND WE COULD FINALLY

37:40.959 --> 37:42.993
QUIT WAITING FOR HIM
TO KNOCK ON THE DOOR,

37:42.995 --> 37:45.211
WE COULD FINALLY BURY HIM,
AND THAT'D BE...

37:45.213 --> 37:47.547
AND JUST THANK GOD

37:47.549 --> 37:50.800
THAT WE WERE FINALLY
GOING TO HAVE...

37:50.802 --> 37:54.554
JUSTICE,
SOMETHING FOR CHRIS.

37:54.556 --> 37:57.290
Narrator:
AS THE TRIAL APPROACHES,
THE FAMILY NOW KNOWS

37:57.292 --> 38:01.561
WHY IT TOOK ALMOST 10 YEARS
FOR THE TRUTH TO COME OUT.

38:01.563 --> 38:03.629
[ GUNSHOT ]

38:03.631 --> 38:05.465
Jen: WE HEARD THAT
RICKY TOLD THE BOYS,

38:05.467 --> 38:07.267
"Y'ALL BETTER NOT SAY
A WORD OF THIS.

38:07.269 --> 38:11.187
DO YOU UNDERSTAND ME?
OR YOU'LL BE NEXT."

38:11.189 --> 38:13.490
Tracie: WHEN CHRIS
FIRST WENT MISSING,

38:13.492 --> 38:15.158
I KNOW THAT THEY
QUESTIONED RICKY,

38:15.160 --> 38:19.145
BUT NOTHING REALLY
CAME OUT OF IT AFTER THAT.

38:19.147 --> 38:21.164
I WAS FRIENDS
WITH RICKY'S PARENTS,

38:21.166 --> 38:25.001
SO OUR FAMILIES HAVE KNOWN
EACH OTHER FOR A LONG TIME.

38:25.003 --> 38:27.170
IT'S JUST SOMETHING
YOU DIDN'T EXPECT.

38:30.992 --> 38:35.045
Narrator: IN FEBRUARY OF 2013,
RICKY MENDOZA STANDS TRIAL

38:35.047 --> 38:40.383
FOR THE MURDER OF
CHRISTOPHER DAIGLE.

38:40.385 --> 38:43.720
SITTING THROUGH
THAT WHOLE TRIAL,

38:43.722 --> 38:47.941
IT WAS LIKE A LIVING HELL.

38:47.943 --> 38:52.011
Jen: RICKY CAME IN WITH
A SMILING FACE AND,

38:52.013 --> 38:53.646
YOU KNOW, LIKE, "HUH.

38:53.648 --> 38:55.982
IT'S 10 YEARS ALREADY, DUDE.

38:55.984 --> 38:57.317
NOTHING'S GOING TO HAPPEN.

38:57.319 --> 38:59.035
IF IT HASN'T
HAPPENED BY NOW,

38:59.037 --> 39:01.571
Y'ALL AIN'T GOING TO
GET ME NOW," YOU KNOW?

39:04.109 --> 39:06.343
AND I GUESS HE RECOGNIZED ME,
BECAUSE WHEN HE LOOKED AT ME,

39:06.345 --> 39:08.745
HE SMILED, WINKED,
AND BLEW A KISS AT ME.

39:10.782 --> 39:15.719
RIGHT THEN IS WHEN I REALIZED
HE'S COLD-BLOODED.

39:18.807 --> 39:21.391
Samantha: IT'S UNBELIEVABLE
THAT SOMEBODY COULD JUST

39:21.393 --> 39:23.893
TAKE IT UPON THEMSELVES
AND SAY,

39:23.895 --> 39:26.896
"OKAY,
YOU LOOKED AT MY GIRL.

39:26.898 --> 39:28.982
I'M GOING TO KILL YOU.

39:28.984 --> 39:32.018
I'M GOING TO TAKE YOU OUT
TO THIS FIELD AND KILL YOU."

39:32.020 --> 39:34.487
Narrator: AFTER ALMOST
TWO WEEKS OF TESTIMONY,

39:34.489 --> 39:38.742
A JURY FINDS RICKY MENDOZA
GUILTY OF MURDER.

39:38.744 --> 39:41.378
WHEN THEY GAVE THAT VERDICT,

39:41.380 --> 39:43.413
IT WAS LIKE
I COULD BREATHE AGAIN.

39:45.667 --> 39:48.701
Tracie: IT WAS FINALLY OVER.

39:48.703 --> 39:50.787
Narrator:
BEFORE RICKY IS SENTENCED,

39:50.789 --> 39:52.589
THE FAMILY WALKS
THROUGH THE FIELD

39:52.591 --> 39:55.375
WHERE CHRIS' PARTIAL REMAINS
WERE DISCOVERED.

39:59.297 --> 40:01.914
Samantha: WE WERE ALL
GOING TO PRAY AND KIND OF HAVE

40:01.916 --> 40:06.469
A LITTLE MEMORIAL SERVICE
FOR CHRIS.

40:06.471 --> 40:10.557
AND WE'RE WALKING ALONG
AND TRUCKS HAD

40:10.559 --> 40:11.724
DRIVEN THROUGH THERE
AND WHATEVER,

40:11.726 --> 40:13.393
SO THERE WERE RUTS.

40:13.395 --> 40:17.430
AND I GUESS IT HAD PUSHED UP,
OR EROSION,

40:17.432 --> 40:20.316
AND YOU COULD SEE
PIECES OF BONE THERE.

40:20.318 --> 40:22.268
WHAT ARE THE ODDS
OF THAT HAPPENING?

40:22.270 --> 40:24.454
[ CRYING ]

40:27.108 --> 40:30.827
Jen: SO WE STARTED DIGGING,
AND THE MORE WE DUG,

40:30.829 --> 40:32.929
THE MORE BONES
WE STARTED TO FIND.

40:34.949 --> 40:37.750
Tracie: IT STILL HURTS
THAT ALL THAT TIME,

40:37.752 --> 40:40.003
HE WAS SO CLOSE,
RIGHT THERE,

40:40.005 --> 40:42.806
JUST MAYBE FOUR MILES
FROM MY HOUSE,

40:42.808 --> 40:44.457
AND I HAD NO IDEA.

40:44.459 --> 40:47.293
THAT WAS HARD.

40:47.295 --> 40:48.761
AND WHEN I
MADE HIM THE PROMISE

40:48.763 --> 40:50.013
I WOULDN'T STOP
TILL I FOUND HIM,

40:50.015 --> 40:52.298
I DIDN'T REALIZE THAT I WAS
GOING TO BE THE ONE

40:52.300 --> 40:55.151
TO ACTUALLY DIG HIM UP.

40:55.153 --> 40:58.605
♪♪

41:00.859 --> 41:02.308
Jen: MY GRANDMA WANDA,

41:02.310 --> 41:06.763
SHE PASSED AWAY
A LITTLE BIT AFTER THE TRIAL.

41:06.765 --> 41:08.364
SHE GOT PEACE
BEFORE SHE PASSED.

41:08.366 --> 41:10.166
SHE KNEW, FINALLY.

41:10.168 --> 41:12.168
IT WAS A LITTLE PEACEFUL
KNOWING THAT THEY WERE

41:12.170 --> 41:13.920
GOING TO BE TOGETHER
FINALLY, YOU KNOW?

41:16.591 --> 41:18.341
Brittany: THERE IS
STILL A LOT OF DAYS

41:18.343 --> 41:21.711
WHERE I WISH THAT
HE WAS STILL AROUND

41:21.713 --> 41:25.381
TO BE ABLE TO CALL OR,
YOU KNOW, GO HAVE A BEER WITH.

41:28.770 --> 41:30.720
I FORGOT THE SOUND
OF HIS VOICE.

41:34.226 --> 41:36.392
I JUST MISS HIM.

41:36.394 --> 41:39.462
♪♪

41:43.702 --> 41:46.703
Tracie: I WISH I KNEW
WHERE CHRIS WOULD BE TODAY

41:46.705 --> 41:48.505
AND WHAT HE WOULD BE DOING.

41:48.507 --> 41:51.324
♪♪

41:53.879 --> 41:56.246
A LOT OF THINGS WERE
TAKEN AWAY FROM ME.

42:00.368 --> 42:02.252
YOU DON'T EVER
GET THOSE BACK.

42:06.725 --> 42:10.894
BUT HE'S IN A BETTER PLACE NOW

42:10.896 --> 42:13.146
AND I'LL SEE HIM
AGAIN ONE DAY.

42:13.148 --> 42:16.182
♪♪
